Headlines.Title: Medical device company Tactile Systems Technology nets $38.3mm in IPO
Headlines.Description: Tactile Systems Technology Inc. (pneumatic compression devices) netted $38.3mm in its Nasdaq IPO of 4.12mm shares (slightly up-sized from 4mm shares at time of filing) at $10 (well below the expected $14-16 per share range).  Proceeds will be used to expand sales, marketing, reimbursement, clinical, regulatory and product development activities, and a portion will also go to pay the cumulative accrued dividends of Series A preferred stockholders.

Headlines.Title: Sophiris FOPO nets $24.2mm
Headlines.Description: Sophiris Bio Inc. (therapeutics for benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate cancer) netted $24.2mm in a public offering of 6.5mm shares at $4. The offering also includes five-year warrants to purchase up to an additional 4.875mm common shares at an exercise price of $4. In June 2016 the company concluded a Phase IIa proof-of-concept study for its localized prostate cancer candidate topsalysin (PRX302), which demonstrated an ability to ablate tumor cells in 50% of patients six months following treatment. Sophiris will use the proceeds from the financing to fund a second Phase II trial of PRX302 to confirm dosing and optimize its targeted delivery. The candidate is also in Phase III for BPH.

Headlines.Title: Xtant Medical announces rights offering to raise up to $10mm
Headlines.Description: Xtant Medical Holdings Inc. (regenerative medicine and medical devices) plans to raise up to $10mm through a rights offering of an undisclosed number of units (each unit will consist of one common share and one warrant to purchase one common share).  The company will use the proceeds to support its growth strategy including increasing surgical instruments and fixation biologics inventory and for R&D and business development needs.

Headlines.Title: Ampio Pharmaceuticals nets $3.5mm in registered direct offering
Headlines.Description: Ampio Pharmaceuticals Inc. (therapies for inflammatory conditions) netted $3.5mm through the sale of 5mm common shares and five-year warrants (to purchase up to 5mm common shares at a strike price of $1) at a combined purchase price of $0.75 (a 17% discount) to an unnamed institutional investor.  The company will use the proceeds to advance the BLA for Ampion (low molecular weight fraction of human serum albumin (HSA) in development for pain due to osteoarthritis of the knee) and for future clinical trials.  Financial West Group served as the placement agent.

Headlines.Description: NVision Medical Corp. (microcatheters for applications in women's health) raised $12mm in a Series B round led by new investor Arboretum Ventures (which added a member to the board), along with returning Series A backers Catalyst Health Ventures, Draper Associates, Seraph Group, LMN Ventures, Astia Angels, and 11 other undisclosed participants, according to its Form D.

Headlines.Title: NVision Medical raises $4.5mm in Series A round
Headlines.Description: Women's health-focused microcatheter device start-up nVision Medical Corp. closed a two-tranche $4.5mm Series A round led by Catalyst Health Ventures (which added a member to the board), and 13 other investors, including Draper Associates, Seraph Group, LMN Ventures, and Astia Angels. The company was founded in January 2012 and is developing microcatheters to access cell samples from the fallopian tubes to screen for ovarian cancer and to detect fallopian tube blockages, which could indicate infertility.

Headlines.Title: ImmunArray raises $1.2mm through seed funding round; later expanded
Headlines.Description: ImmunArray Pvy. Ltd. raised $1.2mm through what appears to be its seed round led by Virginia Life Science Investments; Virginia Life also joined the board of directors. ImmunArray is developing molecular diagnostics based on an exclusive license to the iCHIP technology from the Weizmann Institute of Science. The test will analyze antibodies present in blood, saliva, and other bodily fluids to diagnose disease and monitor therapeutic regimens in autoimmune and inflammatory diseases, as well as caner and other conditions.

Headlines.Title: Series A round brings $3mm to ImmunArray; $2.2mm added in additional closing
Headlines.Description: Molecular diagnostics firm ImmunArray Pvt. Ltd. raised $3mm in the initial closing of a potential $5mm Series A round. Virginia Life Science Investments led and was joined by returning backer the Lazlow Tauber Foundation. ImmunArray is developing the iCHIP technology for analysis of antibody profiles in blood, saliva, and other body fluids for disease diagnosis and prognosis. Potential indications include autoimmune and inflammatory diseases, cancer, and cardiovascular disease. Concurrent with the Series A, the company announced that data from studies of its platform for allograft rejection detection in kidney transplant patients will be presented at an upcoming symposium.

Headlines.Title: MonoSol Rx gets $50mm in debt from Perceptive Advisors
Headlines.Description: Perceptive Advisors provided drug delivery company MonoSol Rx LLC with a $50mm credit facility. MonoSol will use the proceeds to repay an existing debt facility with White Oak Global Advisors ($10mm in June 2008 and $2.5mm in March 2009) and ongoing clinical development of candidates including promising CNS programs.
